cs.CV, cs.CG, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.SI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with shape matching and alignment, which are common problems in computer vision. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is also likely as the paper proposes a novel shape deformation model. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possibility as the paper mentions the efficiency of the proposed method compared to analogous quadratic assignment problem formulations. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is another possibility as the paper presents a convex mixed-integer programming formulation for non-rigid shape matching. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is less likely but still a possibility as the paper mentions the flexibility of the proposed method in handling different variants of matching problems.
